Jenna Etheridge, News24Blue Downs Magistrate's Court (Jenna Etheridge, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A man accused of killing a Cape Town metro policeman is expected to apply for bail in the Blue Downs Magistrate&rsquo;s Court next month.Christopher Jantjies appeared in court on Wednesday in connection with the murder of 53-year-old Constable Ben Koopman.The matter was postponed until November 8 for a bail application.In February this year, Koopman was ambushed, allegedly by two men while walking to his official vehicle outside his home in Eerste River.His service pistol and two-way radio were stolen.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.